Sterigenics US, LLC previously contracted Radian International (Radian) to assist in addressing the requirements under the federal Risk Management Plan as mandated in the Clean Air Act, Section 112(r )(7).  The Risk Management Program rules requires covered facilities to conduct a hazard assessment, develop a prevention and emergency response program, and submit a Risk Management Plan (RMP) to the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency by June 21, 1999.  In 2004 and 2009 Sterigenics completed an update of the the orginal RMP plan by means of using the USEPA software, RMP*Submit.  In 2014, we are submitting the plan via EPAs RMP*eSubmit.



Introduction



Facilities that use or store more than 10,000 lbs. of ethylene oxide are required to prepare and submit a Risk Management Program (RMP) to U.S. EPA.  The RMP consists of several elements, including an evaluation of potential accident scenarios and a comprehensive program to prevent accidental releases of regulated chemicals. 



The RMP summarizes the management, administrative, procedural, and technological controls that work together to minimize the risk of hazardous chemical releases to the community .  The RMP includes the following information:



